rComments: Hands down the best professor in Engineering.

Collins is a genius in his field, one of the most respected professors in my year. Great prof. The only (minor) issue with Collins is the fact that he finds all the material so easy (understandable considering he invented some of the equations he teaches) that he's not afraid to move on to a new topic when students are still lost on the last one.
Best prof in engsci
If you haven't had Collins, you haven't experienced Engsci.

Had a tendency to race through the material (especially important material!) and seemed rather unapproachable. He had little to no office hours. However, his exam is almost identical from year to year - solving these would ensure a high mark on the final, given that you could sift through his scattered notes and random numbers during the course.

Although Professor Collins is a highly educated and intelligent individual, his ability to convey his knowledge to the class is lacking. Rely mostly on the textbook to learn anything, and even then it won't necessarily get you through the assignments. It seems some amount of magical knowledge of something things is needed to pass this class.

Very confusing professor. I don't mind his condescending nature and he is usually joking. He is not good at teaching the material though and is very difficult to follow. He makes somewhat difficult subject matter even harder to understand. I don't understand how he has awards and nominations for lecturing, because I expect much more from my profs.

This is a very difficult course. Prof Collins is a nice guy and his historical anecdotes are very interesting. However his teaching style seems a little dated. He is very arrogant and condescending at times. He believes his teaching and board notes are so good that there's no need for a textbook. As a CIV102 student: WE NEED A TEXTBOOK for ref. !

I hated the subject with a passion, but liked the way he taught. The mini history lessons he gave kept my interest, and his interactions with certain members of the class were nothing short of hilarious. Word of advice to future CIV102 students - do not attempt to show this man how smart you (think you) are. He'll tear you to bits.

Overall, not a good prof. Very arrogant and conceited, has taught the course too many years in a row to tell whether the students understand him or not. I know he is very smart and probably a good guy at heart, but be serious, people, this guy is really overrated.

Excellent professor.  As much as I hate civil engineering, his lectures are actually so interesting I never skip them.  Prof. Collins is a walking encyclopedia and an excellent lecturer.  Whether you like his subject or not, I'm sure you'll enjoy his lectures.

First semester the stuff hes teaching was hard because of our little calculus knowledge... once u understand 2nd order differentials.. then things hes refering to make sense       Awesome lecturer!!! funny story teller   I guess he's just one of the awesome and knowledgeable profs

He knew a lot about civil engineering. He had a lot of experience and exposure in the field. I hated him however cause I do not like civil engineering at all. He went way too fast, I didn't understand anything that was going on. I went to every lecture. 95% of the class loved him, however I hated him...i will never go in civil engineering e

An amazing professor overall, and an integral part of the first-year EngSci experience. Provides interesting historical anecdotes to accompany his concise, clear lectures. His style is very much chalk and talk (although with questions), which may not be to everyone's taste. There is no textbook, just a notebook you fill in and can take to the exam.
Didn't get as much of a kick out of this course as most of my peers did. But he is a knowledgeable prof.

AMAZING prof. Turned a perhaps slightly dull subject into one of the most interesting courses of the semester. In-lecture demonstrations and experiments during tutorials provide an amazing link from theory to practice.
Extremely interested in teaching. Lectures are well planned and it shows.
Demonstration in nearly every class. No textbook, but very clear explanations. CIV102 almost became my favourite course, if it wasn't for Professor Colliander's MAT194 Calculus Class <3.

Makes highly technical subject matter interesting and digestible. Knowledgeable and passionate about his subject and about engineering education in general. The first-year EngSci experience will not be the same after he retires.
decent

Prof. Collins is simply the best professor I've ever had in the first two years of Engsci. He knows pretty much everything there is to know about structures, and he makes jokes that we won't even dare to make. Very friendly person who cares about engineering education.
i love his accent :)
Fantastic professor. Mixes difficult technical concepts with interesting historical anecdotes, really cares about his subject matter.

in short, THE MOST AMAZING PROF/MAN EVER! He seemed to know everything there was to know about everything. an incredibly brilliant man. He made you proud to be an engineer. Great the way he linked historical engineering (er Roman) to what he was talking about. diffinetly the best prof in 1st yr engsci. It was an honour to have him. Funny and smart.
most awesome prof i had in term 1, goes to show for the various awards he won for being a godly lecturer

Rumoured to be very helpful though. My favorite professor.
